p: Table 2 presents the distribution of hrHPV group infection. The percentage of the A9 group infection was higher than that of the A5/A6 group and the A7 group (61.7% of positive cases and 11.1% of all subjects). Single-group infection (83.6% of positive cases and 15.1% of all subjects) more common than multiple-group infection. The most prevalent hrHPV group, in either single or multiple-group infection, was the A9 group. Of single-group infection, 60.8% and 20.8% were from the A9 and A5/A6 groups respectively. Moreover, of multiple-group infection, 66.3% and 73.3% were from the A9 and A5/A6 groups respectively (Table S2). The proportion of the A5/A6 group, A9 group and multiple-group infection in hrHPV positive cases in the Wuhan district were higher than that in the Zhejiang district (31.2% vs. 28.9%, 64.3% vs. 60.9%, 19.8% vs. 15.3%, Ps < 0.001).
